A tragic school shooting in Finland shocked the nation as a teenager gunned down eight people before taking his own life.
The incident, the worst in the country's history, left the community reeling and questioning how such a horrific act could occur.
The shooter, who expressed admiration for violent figures like Hitler and Stalin, posted videos online detailing his plans.
Police found him with hundreds of bullets and a suicide note, indicating a premeditated attack.
The country mourns the loss of innocent lives and struggles to comprehend the senseless violence that unfolded.
